    "truncated_text": "I am writing to the OPM about the proposed reclassification of government workers to Schedule F: Docket ID OPM-2025-0004. Please do not do this.\n\nI firmly believe that politicizing the civil workforce will harm our country. The US's civil workforce, independent FED, and ability to keep much of the government's work in capable, skilled, and nonpartisan hands have allowed the US to become an economic force, a well-respected leader, and a strong nation. Please do not destroy this by adding more political workers to the workforce. \n\nOur country needs an experienced and consistent workforce, not one that is changing with the current president. In our country, we do not have a president for life, we do not have an authoritarian leader,  and we do not have a considerable government workforce that changes every four or eight years. It is the consistency and experience that keep our government functioning well. At the very least, the reason should be that this president cannot fill all the existing political appointments; why add more? But that is not the reason that I am concerned about this proposed change in government workers. Please do not cause more instability in our country. \n\nDo not fire any more government workers. Do not reclassify any government workers. We are losing valuable expertise and skilled workers, gaining nothing in return. Do not add a Schedule F to the government. \n\nThank you.\nCorinne",
